cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "SPARRING Methodology"
message: "If you use SPARRING in your research or methodology, please cite this work."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Niedner"
    given-names: "Barton"
    affiliation: "Resource Forge LLC"
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0003-4117-3426"
repository-code: "https://github.com/muddyone/sparring-publicaccess"
abstract: >
  SPARRING is a methodology for structured AI deliberation in multi-agent
  LLM systems. It addresses compounding LLM failure modes (sycophancy,
  confirmation bias, anchoring, blind spots, hallucinated detail,
  confidently-wrong outputs, bandwagon contamination) by structuring agent
  collaboration into a four-phase ceremony (SPARK, Pattern Lock, The Cut,
  PNP) with two roles (Generator and Challenger) and nine disciplines.
  The repository contains the SPARRING documents, pre-registered
  evaluation pilots, decision packs, condition outputs, partner ratings,
  judge results, analysis scripts, and preprint drafts.
keywords:
  - "structured AI deliberation"
  - "multi-agent LLM"
  - "AI evaluation methodology"
  - "LLM-as-judge"
  - "pre-registration"
  - "agentic AI"
  - "AI safety"
